content: If you look at, say, our office in Austin assets, the entire property there is about 99% leased and with the vacancies coming up, we’re seeing activity to backfill the space even prior to the vacate. So you’re seeing very robust activity in that assets, specifically as a creative office campus that the type of assets we’re looking to gravitate towards and we don’t think it’s a coincidence that that type of asset is drawing that type of attention.
